Category Overview

Our 10 technology categories with corresponding Patlytics analysis groupings. Click any category below to jump to its patents.

CategoryPatentsDescription
3D Reconstruction 6 Building 3D models from 2D images — face reconstruction, depth estimation, scene geometry from a single photo.
Object Detection 12 Identifying and locating objects in images/video — multiscale detection, bounding boxes, feature pyramids.

Image Processing 5 Generating, enhancing, and transforming images — photorealistic synthesis, deblurring, super-resolution.

Reading the Patent Data

Each patent row shows inline badges. Click any patent to expand its full assessment.

FieldSourceWhat It Means
Quality X/9T TechsonPatent strength score (1–9). Factors in claim breadth, prior art exposure, and enforceability. 7+ = strong, 4–6 = moderate, <4 = weak.
$X.XBT TechsonTotal annual revenue of products at risk of infringement by this patent, across all target companies.
Company XX%P PatlyticsHighest claim-element match score for this patent against any product at that company. 100% = every claim element mapped to product evidence.
Score (expanded)P PatlyticsPer-product infringement score (0–100%). Measures how many independent claim elements have documented evidence of use in that product.
Evidence (expanded)P PatlyticsNumber of source documents (patents, publications, product pages) Patlytics found supporting the infringement analysis.
Revenue at RiskT TechsonEstimated revenue exposure for this specific patent, based on the target companies' product revenue.
Prior ArtT TechsonVolume of existing prior art: LOW = less crowded (easier to enforce), HIGH = more prior art to navigate.
Patent StatusT TechsonActive = enforceable, Pending = application filed, Expired = no longer enforceable.

3D Reconstruction

6
Patents covering methods to build 3D models from flat images — including face reconstruction, depth estimation, and scene geometry from a single photo.
WIPOWO/2025/193512A1Single Shot 3D Modelling from 2D Image

Techson Patent Assessment

Not in Techson analysis (WIPO/pre-filing patent)
What This Patent Does
Covers a way to create a full 3D model of any object from a single photograph. The system looks at a flat photo, figures out what the object is, cuts it out from the background, and builds a three-dimensional version you can rotate and view from any angle.
